name: egyptian god series THOTH
description:
Koyung Artwork / egyptian god series #3 /
Thoth (pronounced /θoʊθ/ or /toʊt/) was one of the most important deities in Ancient Egyptian civilization. He is considered the god of writing, the god of virtue, the god of miracles, and the god of the moon. In art, he is often depicted as a person with the head of an ibis or a baboon.
